[Student "S"]
{Your partnership plays Jacoby 2NT convention, so partner's 2NT shows a game-forcing raise in \Ss. Your 3NT bid indicates a 5-card suit and "extra values". Partner's 4\H is a control-bid showing the \HA.  

What you need to know now about partner's hand is Key-Cards so you bid 4NT. He answers 5\S. What is your bid? 

Partner's response says 2 Key-Cards and the \SQ. So you are missing either the trump King or the \DA. So you shouldn't bid 7, but you will almost surely make 6. You bid 6\S.}

