[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown. Yes, you could have jump-shifted on your first bid.  

Slam in \Hs is almost certain, but you should check for Key-Cards. You bid 4NT and partner says 5\C.  

Partner shows 1 or 4 Key-cards. Since he jumped on the second round you figure it must be 4. So you have all the Key-Cards. Time to find out about the other Kings, so you bid 5NT. Partner replies 6\D.  

Partner has 1 King, the only one left, the \DK. You can count about 17 high-card tricks available so you bid 7NT.}

